	Colour image: m x n x 3
	...
	Multi-spectral image: m x n x x


Video: image sequence
	-for human eye: continuous video is minimal: 10 f/s (frames/sec.)




ANALOG TO DIGITAL: 
	AKTER --> ADC (analog digital convertor) --> Digital system --> DAC (digital analog convertor) --> Reproductor/...

	CONTINUOUS FUNCTION ---------------------->  0 and 1 function -------------------------------> aproximation between 0/1 function and Continuos function


	Digitalisation sampling and quantisation ( conversion from continuous func. to 0/1 function --- aproximation)


	SAMPLING:
		audio: deltaT
		image: deltaX and deltaY

	Dynamic range: ratio between min. and max. possible value (of changeable quality)
		-in Decibel dB: 	L_a[dB] = 20 log_10(A_max/A_min) A is amplitude
						L_p[dB] = 10 log_10(P_max/P_min) P is power
					Decibel == počet analógových ÚROVNÍ 
		No of bits in Digital: 8b 12b ...
		( cca. for 1b -- 6dB)

		-Grayscale image: number. of grey levels typically is an integer power of 2: I = 2^k (where k is a number of bits)
		(v podstate v matici MxN je možné mať v jednom mieste hodnotu v rozsahu 2^k kedy 2 je kvoly tomu že to môe byť 0, alebo 1. To je z dôvodu toho že ako zápis sú použité bity a ich počet (k) určuje hornú hranicu 2^k možných hodnot ktoré sa takto dáju zašifrovať.

		-LSB (least significant bit)

		-Quantization error: caused by aproximation of values for levels, or difference between amplitude[-A,A] and quantification/... of levels N
		-SNR signal to Noise Ratio: SNR = P_signal/P_noise, or SNR = (A_signal/A_noise)^2



		Sampling f(t): Diract sampling function/... s(t; deltaT)   --- hodnota v čase T pri samplovacom čase deltaT

		Sampling theorem Nyq, Kotl. Whi..,
			Nyquist: Sampling frequency must be at least twice the highest freqency contained in signal: f_s  >= 2*f_m
					example: max freq. of human hearing 20 KHz, then we are sampling with frequenci of cca. 44.1 KHz
			Aliasing: when Nyquis criterium is violated -- frequenci ... appears as below amplitude


			Moare ..., podvzorkovaný obrazok

